description:
Duties will include but not be limited to:

Drafting speeches, talking points, press releases, media advisories, op-eds, social media copy, and statements for the Member;
Collaborating with the Member, Chief of Staff, and Communications Director to produce speeches;
Working closely with the District Office to ensure accurate and appropriate messaging of local priorities;
Working closely with the legislative team to ensure accurate and appropriate messaging of the Member’s policy priorities;
Executing other press responsibilities as needed and assigned.

This position reports to the Chief of Staff.
